main event: Two shiny silver cigar-shaped objects with bright flaming tails were spotted over Muleshoe, Texas in 1963.
interesting points: The objects moved rapidly, curving and zigzagging, and then dove and exploded like a fireworks display.
Two smaller cigar-shaped objects also appeared and disappeared at high speed.
The sighting was reported by multiple observers, including a farmer, traffic controllers, and a maintenance test pilot, who were all considered highly reliable.
No sound was reported from the objects.
The objects were observed for only a few seconds to up to 30 seconds.
sighted object: two silver cigar-shaped objects, with two smaller objects also reported
witnesses: farmer, traffic controllers, maintenance test pilot
photographs: no, the report does not include photographs
